-- China, Nigeria Sign $900 Million Rail, Communications Accord, Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-20T23:48:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/china-nigeria-sign-900-million-rail-communications-accord-xinhua-says.html
China and Nigeria signed a $900
million credit agreement for rail and communications projects in
the African nation, the official Xinhua News Agency reported,
citing Nigerian Finance Minister Olusegun Aganga.  The funding, provided by the Export-Import Bank of China,
includes $500 million for the Abuja rail project and $400
million for a national public security communications project,
Xinhua reported late yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
